  <marc:subfield code="6">520-00//r</marc:subfield>
  <marc:subfield code="a">This is a manuscript of the Yom Kippur Mah&#x323;zor for the rite of  L'Isle-sur-la-Sorgue written and signed by Eliyahu Delpuget on 24 Adar (II) 423 (Monday April 2, 1663; colophon contains a mistaken chronogram from Leviticus 23:27: &#x5D9;&#x5D5;"&#x5DD; &#x5D4;&#x5DB;&#x5E4;&#x5E8;&#x5D9;"&#x5DD; &#x5D4;&#x5D5;"&#x5D0;, which equals 427, or 1667). The texts are written out in full, repeating the multiple Selih&#x323;ot with Piyutim and poetic material. For a number of the Piyutim early on in the manuscript, the scribe attributes the poem to a composer and sometimes describes the poem layout; this stops in the Shah&#x323;arit prayers (after f. 98v). Some of the captions for the Selih&#x323;ot include Pizmon, Ofan, Selih&#x323;ah, Toh&#x323;akhah and Al-khrug (&#x5D0;&#x5DC; &#x5DB;&#x5E8;&#x5D5;&#x5D2;); perhaps this is related to the Arabic al-khuru&#x304;j.</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
